  <span id="freeText17472712328691470668" style="display:none">Having dived into a mystery novel after so long with a skeptic mind, I found it gradually reduced to a mere tinge. I had myself engaged throughout the whole book yet I was disappointed to find out I already had figured the mysterious figure half way through the book. Now, as I close the book and get to collect my final thoughts on this one, would I recommend this to anyone? As a matter of fact, yes. Even with certain degree of predictability, Agatha Christie will hold you through the journey with her writing. You will find yourself bewildered over the most familiar scene in a different shade.</span>
