  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3818639612" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3818639612" />
    <a title="Karina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/62428250-karina"><img alt="Karina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1632727821p2/62428250.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3818639612?book_show_action=true">Feb 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karina" href="/user/show/62428250-karina">Karina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3818639612" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9503398052463418552">This was a good recommendation from a few of my friends here and I thank them so much because this was fantastic and fast paced.<br/><br/> I loved how Hercule Poirot (now retired) found the murderer and the most insignificant clues to be very significant. He enlisted the help of a well-known village doctor (the narrator) and went about asking and prodding and figuring. I never saw it coming. And the ending!! WOW.<br/><br/>One of my favorite thus far.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

